Zee One is so excited to celebrate the 2022 Valentine’s Day with Bollywood love stories. Viewers, according to a statement from StarTimes, will be enjoying an entire month of love themed movies and drama series on Zee One. Zee One, a sister channel of Zee World, is a solely Bollywood oriented channel on StarTimes. “With romantic dramas, romantic series and romantic comedies, we will be speaking the language of love fluently this February! If your love language is quality time, then there is no better time and place to plan a date night right in front of your screen with Zee One any day this month,” Ejiro Okene, CEO, DeepVision, the media buying representatives of Zee One in Nigeria said.   Real reason Ken Caleb-Olumese opted to lease out The…     Aso believes working hard will leave huge legacy in the…     Netflix eyes King Of Boys’ editor Steve Sodiya   Some of the Bollywood productions scheduled to whet the audience appetite on Zee One in February includes ‘Happy Bhaag Jayegi,’ which will air on February 5, Jaane Tu… Ya Jaane Na on February 6, Love Express on February 14, Baaghi on February 19, Do Lafzon Ki Kahani on February 20, Kedarnath on February 21, and Behen Hogi Teri on February 27. “So, whether you want to go from ‘bud’ to bae or rekindle the romance, Zee One will be your personal cupid.  Catch all these movies at 3pm daily on Zee One channel on StarTimes,” Ejiro said. - Advertisement - Also new on Zee One this month is a drama series titled Sacred Ties which replaces Reach for The Stars at 6pm. Sacred Ties follows the love story of Manav and Arhana as they embark on a rollercoaster of passion and betrayal. Rasika plans to manipulate Satish and his family with lies about Archana. Sunanda also uses the opportunity to expose Manav’s secrets.